                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3154.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-11T22:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1912—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The German Minister called to-day to inform me that he had been instructed to
                    pursue a course analogous to that of our Government in removal of Germans from
                    dangerous localities and if necessary from the country.</p>
                <p>The organization of Americans and other foreigners in Mexico City is going
                    forward with great success.</p>
                <p>The President’s proclamation, after being fully read and understood, has had a
                    most beneficial effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
